                Ways with words<br>
                A. The words in the crossword puzzle are from the text. Find them in the text to solve the puzzle based
                on the clues given below.<br><br>
                Down:<br>
                1. to be preoccupied with a single topic or emotion - obsessed<br>
                3. to move slowly and quietly in a particular direction - creep<br>
                4. orderly, logical and Consistent - coherent<br>
                <br>
                Across:<br>
                2. to utter rapidly or unintelligibly - babble<br>
                5. to insert something between other things - interpose<br>
                6. an unreadable handwriting - squiggle<br>
